Tester Responsibilities:
1. Check whether all features are working properly.
2. Find bugs in the application.
3. Report the bugs to the developer.

Example:
Before the app is released, the tester checks all the features and reports any problems.

Test Leader Responsibilities:
1. Make the testing plan.
2. Give testing work to the team members.
3. Check whether all testing is completed before release.

Example:
Before releasing the app, the Test Leader checks that all important bugs are fixed and then approves the release.